## core componets 
health check - tests wheater backend servers are working. if it fails
the loadblaancer stops sending traffice to it 

layer 7 load balancer -- this works at the application layer 
(http/https)  instead of just forwarding traffic it understands web requests and can rout them to different 
backend services based on rules 

backend services- is the group of resourses that actually handel the traffic,
this is usually a group of VM instances.

instance group- a collection of VM's that are treated as one backend 
the load balancer distributs the traffice across these machines.

frontend- the public entry point of the loadbalancer. it provides the 
external IP address where users connect.

